author: Google
description: Live from Mountain View, Logan Kilpatrick, Amaar Reshi, Kat Kampf, Tulsee Doshi and other guests are here to show how you can bring any idea to life with Gemini 3 in AI Studio. They will vibe code apps live to showcase various functionalities (one-shot, iteration, deployment, sharing, “I’m Feeling Lucky”) and features (Nano Banana, Maps Grounding, Live API) of AI Studio’s build tab.
title: Vibe coding with Gemini 3 — live from Mountain View

description:
Gemini 3 Pro is rolling out globally starting today. To use it, simply select “Thinking” from the model selector. Our Google AI Plus, Pro and Ultra subscribers will continue to enjoy higher limits. We’re also extending our free year of Google AI Pro to U.S. college students, ensuring they have access to the best of Google AI, including Gemini 3. Terms apply.

author: Google
description:
Gemini 3 is rolling out globally starting today. Try it at gemini.google.com by selecting “Thinking” from the model picker.

Upload a video to get a detailed analysis on your favorite teams and players, or upload your own vid to perfect your personal technique. Gemini 3 in the Gemini app will: 

- Evaluate videos up to an hour long for Pro or Ultra subscribers
- Provide detailed visual analysis, complete with time stamps
- Breakdown strengths, weaknesses and opportunities 
- Guide you through ways to improve

author: Google
description:
Introducing Gemini 3, our most intelligent model with state-of-the-art reasoning, deep multimodal understanding and powerful agentic capabilities. It’s now available in Google Search, starting with AI Mode. Gemini 3 brings incredible reasoning power to Search because it’s built to grasp unprecedented depth and nuance for your hardest questions. It also unlocks new generative UI experiences so you can get dynamic visual layouts with interactive tools and simulations — generated specifically for you.
